# DealershipScanner — agent standards

## Scope and edits

- Change only what the task requires; no drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
- Match existing naming, imports, and style in touched files.

## Security

- Follow `docs/SECURITY_MASTER_TODO.md` for all security work (see companion rule *security-master-todo-workflow*).
- Prefer parameterized SQL; never interpolate user input into SQL strings.
- No `shell=True` for subprocess; validate high-risk inputs (URLs, IDs) before spawning processes.

## Quality

- Prefer clear errors over silent `except: pass` for operator-visible behavior.
- Run validation steps from the master todo when completing a security item.

## Communication

- Use proper code citations (`startLine:endLine:path`) when referencing existing code.
- Write complete sentences; avoid filler and engagement bait.
